org.hps.monitoring.application.model

Class ConfigurationModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.monitoring.application.model.AbstractModel
      • org.hps.monitoring.application.model.ConfigurationModel

  • public final class ConfigurationModel
extends AbstractModel
    A model of the global configuration parameters that can be used to automatically update the GUI from a configuration or push changes from GUI components into the current configuration.

      • setDetectorName

        public void setDetectorName(String detectorName)
        Set the detector to load from the detector model resources in the jar.

        These are present in the jar according to the LCSim convention: 

         ${DETECTOR_NAME}/detector.properties

        where detector.properties has the name of the detector matching the directory name.

        Parameters:
        detectorName - the name of the detector name

      • setEtName

        public void setEtName(String etName)
        Set the name of the ET system which is usually a file.

        Setting this to a valid file on disk being used by the ET server to buffer events will result in event processing speedup.

        Parameters:
        etName - the name of the ET system (usually a path on disk used as an event buffer by an ET server)
